briefdescription.para: Called when asyn clients call pasynOctet->write().

detaileddescription.para:
This function performs actions for some parameters, including BPC, and Chips/DACS. For all parameters it sets the value in the parameter library and calls any registered callbacks..
pasynUser
pasynUser structure that encodes the reason and address.
value
Address of the string to write.
nChars
Number of characters to write.
nActual
Number of characters actually written.

pasynUser
asynUser structure that contains the function code in pasynUser->reason.
value
The value for this parameter
Takes action if the function code requires it. Currently only ADShutterControl requires action here. This method is normally called from the writeInt32 method in derived classes, which should set the value of the parameter in the parameter library.

This method calls the report function in the asynPortDriver base class. It then calls the NDArrayPool::report() method if details >5.
fp
File pointed passed by caller where the output is written to.
details
If >5 then NDArrayPool::report and NDAttributeList::report are both called.

briefdescription.para: Simple function that prints all information about a connected camera.
Function responsible for starting camera image acqusition.

detaileddescription.para: First, check if there is a camera connected. Then, set camera values by reading from PVs. Then, we execute the Acquire Start command. if this command was successful, image acquisition started.

simplesect.para: : status -> error if no device, camera values not set, or execute command fails. Otherwise, success

briefdescription.para: Function responsible for stopping camera image acquisition.

detaileddescription.para: First check if the camera is connected. If it is, execute the 'AcquireStop' command. Then set the appropriate PV values, and callParamCallbacks

simplesect.para: : status -> error if no camera or command fails to execute, success otherwise

briefdescription.para: Checks whether the directory specified BCP/DACS/Raw parameter exists.

detaileddescription.para: This is a convenience function that determines the directory specified BCP/DACS/Raw Path parameter exists. It sets the value of xxxPathExists to 0 (does not exist) or 1 (exists). It also adds a trailing '/' character to the path if one is not present. Returns a error status if the directory does not exist.

briefdescription.para: Checks whether the directory specified exists.

detaileddescription.para: This is a convenience function that determines the directory specified exists. It adds a trailing '/' or '\' character to the path if one is not present. It returns true if the directory exists and false if it does not
